Former nominated MP Mark Too dies at St Luke&rsquo;s Hospital in Eldoret where he had been rushed in critical condition this afternoon.Mark Too formely known as &lsquo;Bwana Dawa&rsquo; has died aged 60&nbsp;after short-term illness. Too was Former nomited MP of Kapsaret in Uasin Gishu County during Kanu regime. The late legislator was a close right-hand man of the former President Daniel Moi.